reviews.text:
Potential, without skill. This restaurant seemed so exciting when we first arrived, but we were sat at a dirty table, and left without menus, or even a greeting for half an hour. It took an additional 15 minutes to bring a coffee and a juice, and an additional 45 minutes for our food to arrive. We had four tables around get up and leave while arguing with the owner.

I was excited once it finally came, having decided to stick it out in hopes it would be worth it all, but was horribly disappointed at cold food that had been dying in the window.

I do not recommend at this time.

We absolutely loved our experience here. The staff was great and the food was fantastic. We absolutely enjoyed our experience here and would highly recommend it. From the pastas to the sandwiches to the lemonade.

The buffalo chicken flatbread, the pasta and the half chicken with a side of the lemonade is what I would recommend. My burger did have a hard bread - it was extra toasted but the rest of the burger was solid. The server took a while to take our order as well but might have just been overwhelmed by orders.

Fast, friendly and wonderful food. Upbeat atmosphere and clean.

We had the gyro, beef shawarma wrap and the chicken sandwich. All had unique flavors and were carefully prepared. We shared baklava and the bread pudding and they were stunning. Everything was made on the premises. We live 4 hours away, but we will come back!

We went in after checking the website and seeing the beautiful breakfast options. Unfortunately, the only negative thing I have to say is, that breakfast is not served all day. We stayed for lunch and the servings were huge for the prices. I had a mango lemonade and it was delicious. The staff is friendly and the restaurant is very clean. They serve halal, and vegan/vegetarian options. I would come back again to try their breakfast. Oh, they also have baklava and cake selections.

Thrilled to find this spot on the same block as the hotel I was staying at while in town visiting Cleveland Clinic.

Great service and great food. Got a customized omelette that was phenomenal. Lots of veggies and protein options available. I really liked the gyro meat I got in mine.

They also have a variety of Egyptian menu options that I'd love to try.

Word of caution, this restaurant is halal so there is no pork. Instead they offer turkey sausage and turkey bacon which were both tasty.

editorial_summary.overview: Easygoing, low-key outlet offering classic comfort food staples from pancakes to hummus to pasta.

I had an appt at the Cleveland Cljnic.  While there, having fasted for 14 hours, I looked for a restaurant nearby that had an interesting menu. Urban Kitchen fit the bill. Our Falafel Bites were fantastic. My Reuben was great, real Deli quality. I had a homemade Peach Iced Tea that was the best I've ever had. I highly recommend Urban Kitchen.

I usually don‚Äôt like to leave a poor review but unfortunately this situation calls for it. We are here visiting a patient at Cleveland clinic & decided to take time out of an already long sad day to grab a bite. We had heard great things about Urban Kitchen so was excited to check it out. We are immediately greeted by the staff and sat down. Server comes to the table we chat about the menu and put in our order. We got a quesadilla for the app and 2 entrees. All the food comes out together, strange. We bring it to the servers attention, he offers to keep our entrees hot on the line, we declined. My aunt previously asked for extra sauce when she placed her order but the food came without it. We had to wait 7-10 mins before the server came back to let him know about the sauce. At this point the food is cold. We brought all of this to their attention and mind you there was a clear attitude. We asked to speak with a manger, apparently no manager on duty. Strange. My thing is you all are a restaurant next to a hospital. Most of your business probably comes from that campus. Have empathy, have a better attitude, have better hospitality. You should have that anyway as a restaurant but even more so because of the location. We come to Cleveland clinic quite often and we will never come back to this establishment. Control your attitude.

So glad I found this place. We were looking for a place to each lunch after the Congenital Heart Walk at Wade Oval. Great atmosphere and delicious food. So fresh & flavorful. The portions were generous and priced right.  Our server was kind. We will definitely go back now that we found this gem.

I highly recommend this place if you are looking for a good place to eat that's affordable and you get what you pay for! Like everyone said in the previous reviews, they are generous with portions. Thanks Calvin who was our server. We will be back

I had the Chipotle shrimp and chicken Alfredo.  The shrimp was excellent and the Alfredo sauce had just the right heat. I can not recommend this restaurant enough. We went to The Urban Kitchen on a recommendation and thankfully now have a new fabulous restaurant to go to. We will be back.... & back & back & back!!!!!

The food is mix of Egyptian dishes, American cuisine and Mediterranean flavors and dishes. Something for everyone and the prices are reasonable.

detailedReviews.text: The grape leaves were delicious and my aunt enjoyed her chicken sandwich.

detailedReviews.author: Amy Harris
detailedReviews.text: It was a moderately busy lunch and there were a few servers on staff and several in the kitchen.   We waited a very long time to give our order and then 30 minutes just to get fountain sodas!!  45 minutes for food?!.  Other customers had walked out.  No idea what the issue was; no explanation given.  Food was average. One of the guests in our party asked for no cheese on the sandwich, but it was still served with cheese.  Not impressed.  Won‚Äôt be back. There are better lunch options in the city overall.

detailedReviews.author: F Chang
detailedReviews.text: We were dining as a party of four, and they brought out the food for three of us in a reasonable time.  Our fourth party member didn't get her food for another half hour!  Also, don't dine here if you don't like salty food.  Everything is pre salted to an excessive degree, even if you ask them to not add any salt at all.  Finally, the kitchen does not handle allergies well, even when given an allergy card with all allergies listed.

detailedReviews.author: La Carter
detailedReviews.text: I can't get my mind off of the Mediterranean omelette-DELISH. It was my first time having it, but definitely won't be the last. Cozy atmosphere and friendly staff- I love it all. Thank you.

detailedReviews.author: Swapna Kiran
detailedReviews.text: Heavy pine sol smell, unable to sit and eat. The food smelled like pine sol after a while. The water glasses were not washed properly, hair on cucumber pickle. Nauseous and Horrible service. Food quantity was good but service was bad.

detailedReviews.author: Karen Tunnell (Me)
detailedReviews.text: The food is so amazing. If you go to Cleveland, Ohio you need to go to this restaurant. I tried the stuffed French Toast and was not disappointed. I only wish they were where I  lived.

detailedReviews.author: Tori Smith
detailedReviews.text: This place is amazing, it was my first time here but my mom praises this place. The owner is wonderful, and everything is so fresh and tasty. Excellent service and atmosphere too. It's a must stop in Cleveland!

detailedReviews.author: Alison Grenon
detailedReviews.text: The omelette was so fresh and fluffy and great portions. The staff was very friendly, welcoming, and attentive. Expansive menu with a lot of variety and options. Amazing Turkish coffee!! We can‚Äôt wait to come back for another meal.

detailedReviews.author: Barbie Edington
detailedReviews.text: Tasty hot meal. Fast & friendly service. The food smelled amazing when we walked in! Everyone was kind and service was quick. Everything was very flavorful! We will be back!

detailedReviews.author: Coty Mitchell
detailedReviews.text: Really nice place. been here a few times they are always so nice they  got the food to the table in good time

detailedReviews.author: Jeff

detailedReviews.author: Potato Spud
detailedReviews.text: The food was amazing (a little pricy for the entrees but not terrible). Our waitress was great but be careful ordering the items that aren‚Äôt marked as quick because it took forever to actually get out food.

detailedReviews.author: Steve Steinolfson
detailedReviews.text: Great salads!  Fresh and very Impressed with lunch

detailedReviews.author: Ronald Edwards
detailedReviews.text: I got pancakes, Turkey bacon and eggs. The atmosphere was nice and clean. The breakfast was really good and cooked the way that I requested! I will definitely come back again!

detailedReviews.author: brittany sokolowski
detailedReviews.text: Great meal!!

detailedReviews.author: Latrice
detailedReviews.text: Great food, great service and affordable prices. The breakfast slammer is a hit! Love  the new look/renovations!

detailedReviews.author: Daniel B
detailedReviews.text:
The vibe is family. The food was wonderful.  We leaned into the Egyptian with the chicken Molokhya and Mashawi.  Chicken was moist and fall off the bone with the green sauce (soup?) that was herbaceous and delicious.  Mashawi was a delight of flavors on an open bread. The peppers were grilled into smoky candy because they brought out all the natural sugars. The meats were delightful and went with the garlic sauce perfectly.

This is my third time through Cleveland recently and third time eating here. Love it!!

Oh and the okra stew is just the best!!!!!

detailedReviews.author: Rob Roy
detailedReviews.text: The food is amazing.  The Molokhai Stew and Chicken dish is unreal.  Authentic and delicious

detailedReviews.author: Ken Ray
detailedReviews.text: Great fresh food ,and great ambiance. Hoping urban kitchen opens more restaurants
